A ranar Lahadi da kuma Asabar da yamma, manyan kantunan Woolworth da Coles na Australia sun rage iyakar sayen kayan wanka zuwa biyu da kuma kunshin daya a kowane ma'amala a duk shagunan da ke kasar.
ALDI ta kuma kafa iyaka ta fakiti guda, a ranar Litinin.
An sanar da wannan takunkumi a matsayin sako a akwatin kudi da kuma shafin Facebook na kamfanin.
An bayar da rahoton cewa masu siye suna tara kayayyaki saboda tsoron COVID-19 idan jama'a suka yi keɓewa.
A ranar Laraba, Woolworths ta kuma rage sayen kayan wanka don isar da kaya zuwa gida zuwa fakiti ɗaya a kowane oda.
Wannan canjin ya biyo bayan iyakancewar fakiti huɗu a kowace ma'amala da Woolworths da Coles suka yi a ranar 4 da 5 ga Maris.
A cikin sanarwar da ya fitar a ranar 8 ga watan Maris, Coles ya ruwaito cewa tare da sanya takunkumin a kan fakitin guda hudu, "yawancin shagunan har yanzu suna da isasshen kaya a cikin awa daya da isar da su", yana mai kiran bukatar "marasa misali", yayin da ALDI, a cikin wani sakon Facebook a ranar Talata, ya kira ta "ba zato ba tsammani".
Sayarwa ta "hujja" a makon da ya gabata, a cewar wani mai magana da yawun Woolworths.
Costco a Canberra ma ya takaita adadin da aka yarda da shi zuwa fakiti biyu a makon da ya gabata.
Don kauce wa ƙarancin, Coles ya ba da umarnin ƙarin marufi daga masu samarwa da haɓaka yawan jigilar kayayyaki, Woolworths ya ba da umarnin ƙarin kayan aiki, yayin da ALDI ke ba da kayan aiki don ayyukan musamman na ranar Laraba.
Russell Zimmerman, shugaban hukumar Retailers Association of Australia, ya ce 'yan kasuwa suna kokarin kara yawan kayayyaki, amma takunkumin da hukumomin karamar hukuma suka kafa game da lokacin da za a kai motocin ya sa hakan ya yi wuya.
Ya yi tsammanin farashin samarwa zai karu, yayin da masu samarwa ke kokarin biyan bukatar, da kuma karancin tallace-tallace na musamman.
